content: In the following problems, you will be given a series of propositions as premises and a proof obligation. The premises are in the form '(1) xxx. (2) xxx. (3) xxx. ...', and the proof obligation is in the form 'Prove: (n) xxx.' You need to provide the minimal set of premise propositions such that the proof obligation can be derived from the given premises. You should present the result in the form '(1),(2),(3),...->(n)', where the propositions on the left side of the arrow are separated by commas and represent the premise numbers, and the right side of the arrow represents the proof obligation number. Please ensure that the propositions on the left side of the arrow are presented in the order of their introduction in the proof process, meaning each proposition's introduction must be consistent with the derivation process (for example, the first two propositions might derive an intermediate conclusion, which then can be combined with a third proposition for further derivation). The answer should only be in the form '(1),(2),(3),...->(n)' without any additional text.(Here is an example: [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'Premises: [(1) Each zumpus is a jompus and a yumpus. (2) Dumpuses are opaque and tumpuses. (3) Sterpuses are lempuses and impuses. (4) Every vumpus is a shumpus and a zumpus. (5) Grimpuses are brimpuses and rompuses. (6) Every numpus is a grimpus. (7) Each brimpus is a lorpus and a wumpus. (8) Rompuses are sterpuses and vumpuses. (9) Stella is a grimpus and a brimpus. (10) Stella is a yumpus and a jompus.] Prove: (11) Stella is a vumpus.'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '(9),(5),(8)->(11)'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Premises: [(1) Stella is a yumpus and a jompus. (2) Stella is a grimpus and a brimpus. (3) Rompuses are sterpuses and vumpuses. (4) Each brimpus is a lorpus and a wumpus. (5) Every numpus is a grimpus. (6) Grimpuses are brimpuses and rompuses. (7) Every vumpus is a shumpus and a zumpus. (8) Sterpuses are lempuses and impuses. (9) Dumpuses are opaque and tumpuses. (10) Each zumpus is a jompus and a yumpus.] Prove: (11) Stella is a vumpus.'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '(2),(6),(3)->(11)'}])

Premises: [(1) Each yumpus is nervous. (2) Every yumpus is a tumpus. (3) Numpuses are rompuses. (4) Each sterpus is an impus. (5) Each rompus is not fast. (6) Each numpus is angry. (7) Jompuses are hot. (8) Tumpuses are numpuses. (9) Each rompus is a sterpus. (10) Dumpuses are not transparent. (11) Numpuses are grimpuses. (12) Every brimpus is sweet. (13) Every grimpus is not dull. (14) Vumpuses are gorpuses. (15) Tumpuses are muffled. (16) Every zumpus is overcast. (17) Every vumpus is brown. (18) Sterpuses are brimpuses. (19) Each sterpus is not large. (20) Each rompus is a zumpus. (21) Every yumpus is a jompus. (22) Every tumpus is a dumpus. (23) Max is a yumpus. (24) Max is a vumpus.] Prove: (25) Max is not large.

[(1) Each yumpus is nervous. (2) Every yumpus is a tumpus. (3) Numpuses are rompuses. (4) Each sterpus is an impus. (5) Each rompus is not fast. (6) Each numpus is angry. (7) Jompuses are hot. (8) Tumpuses are numpuses or dumpuses. (9) Each rompus is a sterpus or a zumpus. (12) Every brimpus is sweet. (13) Every grimpus is not dull. (14) Vumpuses are gorpuses and not other kinds of pusses. (15) Tumpuses are muffled and overcast.]

→ (25) Max is not large, because each rompus is a sterpus or a zumpus, and each rompus is not fast, so Max cannot be a large rompus.

(2)-(3), (6)-(7), (9)-(10), (14)-(16), and (20)-(23) → (25)

This minimal set of premise propositions proves the proof obligation.

Premises: [(1) Max is a vumpus. (2) Max is a yumpus. (3) Every tumpus is a dumpus. (4) Every yumpus is a jompus. (5) Each rompus is a zumpus. (6) Each sterpus is not large. (7) Sterpuses are brimpuses. (8) Every vumpus is brown. (9) Every zumpus is overcast. (10) Tumpuses are muffled. (11) Vumpuses are gorpuses. (12) Every grimpus is not dull. (13) Every brimpus is sweet. (14) Numpuses are grimpuses. (15) Dumpuses are not transparent. (16) Each rompus is a sterpus. (17) Tumpuses are numpuses. (18) Jompuses are hot. (19) Each numpus is angry. (20) Each rompus is not fast. (21) Each sterpus is an impus. (22) Numpuses are rompuses. (23) Every yumpus is a tumpus. (24) Each yumpus is nervous.] Prove: (25) Max is not large.

根据给定的前提，可以得出以下推论：

(1) Max是vumpus → Max是gorpus
(2) Max是yumpus → Max是tumpus
(3) 每个tumpus是dumpus
(4) 每个yumpus是jompus
(5) 每个rompus是zumpus
(6) 每个sterpus不是大的
(7) Sterpuses是brimpuses
(8) 每个vumpus是brown的
(9) 每个zumpus是overcast的
(10) Tumpuses是muffled的
(11) Vumpuses是gorpus
(12) 每个grimpus不是dull的
(13) 每个brimpus是sweet的
(14) Numpuses是grimpuses → Numpuses是rompuses
(15) Dumpuses不是透明的
(16) 每个rompus是sterpus
(17) Tumpuses是numpuses → Tumpuses和numpuses属于同一类别
(18) Jompuses是hot的
(19) 每个numpus生气 → 每个numpus是rompuses中的一种
(20) 每个rompus不是快的 → Max不是快的rompus
(21) 每个sterpus是impus → Impuses和sternpus属于同一类别

根据以上推论，可以得出结论：Max不是大的。因为每个rompus是sterpus或zumpus，且每个rompus不是大的，所以Max不能是一个大的rompus。因此，前提集合可以得出(25) Max不是大的。
